# Full-Stack SvelteKit App with PostgreSQL and Prisma ORM

I'll guide you through building a full-stack application using SvelteKit (for frontend and backend), PostgreSQL (database), and Prisma (ORM). This will create a simple blog app with CRUD operations, demonstrating the stack.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js (v16+ recommended)
- PostgreSQL installed locally or a cloud instance (e.g., Supabase)
- Git for cloning if needed

## Step 1: Set Up SvelteKit Project
Use the official SvelteKit template:
```bash
npm create svelte@latest my-project && cd my-project
npm install
```
Choose the default options (Skeleton project, no TypeScript add-on yet).

## Step 2: Install Dependencies
Add Prisma and PostgreSQL client:
```bash
npm install prisma @prisma/client pg
npm install -D @types/pg  # For TypeScript support if needed
```

## Step 3: Configure Database and Prisma
1. Create a `.env` file in the project root:
   ```
   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/myproject?schema=public"
   ```
   Replace with your PostgreSQL credentials.

2. Initialize Prisma:
   ```bash
   npx prisma init
   ```

3. Define the schema in `prisma/schema.prisma`:
   ```prisma
   generator client {
     provider = "prisma-client-js"
   }

   datasource db {
     provider = "postgresql"
     url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
   }

   model Post {
     id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
     title     String
     content   String?
     published Boolean  @defaults(false)
     authorId  Int
     author    User     @relation(fields: [authorId], references: [id])
     createdAt DateTime @default(now())
   }

   model User {
     id    Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
     email String  @unique
     name  String?
     posts Post[]
   }
   ```

4. Run migrations:
   ```bash
   npx prisma db push
   npx prisma generate
   ```

## Step 4: Set Up SvelteKit Backend (API Routes)
SvelteKit uses file-system based routing. Create API endpoints in `src/routes/api/`.

- `src/routes/api/posts/+server.ts` (Handle GET all posts and POST new post):
  ```typescript
  import { json } from '@sveltejs/kit';
  import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';

  const prisma = new PrismaClient();

  export async function GET() {
    const posts = await prisma.post.findMany({
      include: { author: true },
    });
    return json(posts);
  }

  export async function POST({ request }) {
    const { title, content, authorId } = await request.json();
    const post = await prisma.post.create({
      data: { title, content, authorId: parseInt(authorId), published: true },
    });
    return json(post);
  }
  ```

- Create similar routes for `users` and specific post updates/deletes (e.g., `src/routes/api/posts/[id]/+server.ts`).

